sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M1727
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part was designed for a class and is not available. It contains a pBAD promoter, a standard RBS, the coding region for Hepcidin, a 6x repeat of spider silk, and a 10x histidine tag, followed by a double stop codon.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Hepcidin has been optimized for expression in E. coli
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Richard Decker

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M1721
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Optimized Hepcidin + 6x spider silk + 10x His Tag
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Optimized sequence based on AA sequence available on NCBI for hepcidin from crocodile blood.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part was designed for a class and does not really exist. It is comprised of the part BBa_M1716, which is optimized hepcidin, 6 repeats of the part BBa_K844004, and part BBa_K844000, which is a 10x His tag.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Optimzed for expression in E. coli.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Richard Decker

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K844000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: 10x-Histidine tag with double stop codon TAATAA to allow for better extraction of tagged products and protein termination in a single part.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kathleen Miller

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M1720
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The part comes from the AA sequence for hepcidin, but has been optimized for E. coli.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part was designed for a class and does not really exist. It is comprised of the part BBa_M1718, which is a combination of Optimized hepcidin and spider silk, and 5 repeats of the part BBa_K844004.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Optimized for E. coli using NCBI OPTIMIZER.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Richard Decker

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K844004
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Spider Silk 1x Subunit "B" (Balanced tRNA codon optimized)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Artificially designed based on BBa_K844002 and DNA was synthesized
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Spider silk subunit optimized to use a more balanced, but still greatly reduced, number of tRNA codons; contains two elasticity domains and one strength domain.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Andrea Halling

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M1718
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Both protein coding regions are based on original AA sequences, but have been optimized for expression in E. coli.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is for a class project and does not really exist. The part combines the part BBa_M1716 that codes for the E. coli optimized hepcidin protein with part BBa_K844004, which codes for a single coding region of spider silk protein.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Richard Decker

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M1716
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: NCBI OPTIMIZER using AA sequence from GenBank number ADA68357.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Richard Decker
